OVERVIEW:
SectorWars 2102 ship catalog featuring 8 vessel types (3 trading, 2 combat, 3 specialized) with distinct stats for cargo, drones, speed, defense, and special abilities. Ships upgradeable across 7 categories with insurance options.

FACTS:
* 8 ship types: Light Freighter, Cargo Hauler, Fast Courier, Defender, Carrier, Colony Ship, Scout Ship, Warp Jumper
* Starting ship: Light Freighter (10,000 credits, received at first login)
* Speed measured in sectors/turn (0.4 to 2.5 range)
* Defense: shields and hull points (separate damage absorption layers)
* Cargo capacity: 100-1000 units baseline
* Drone capacity: 0-12 drones (1000 credits each)
* Genesis capacity: 0-5 devices per ship
* All ships upgradeable in 7 categories
* Insurance available: Basic (50%), Standard (75%), Premium (90%)
* Ship destruction: eject to escape pod, lose ship and cargo, keep credits
* Warp Jumper: unique acquisition (500k credits, special materials, 3-5 days build time)

TERMINOLOGY:
* Sectors/Turn: Distance ship travels per turn (modified by upgrades)
* Shield Points: First layer of defense, regenerates when docked
* Hull Points: Second layer of defense, requires repair when damaged
* Drone Capacity: Maximum autonomous combat units ship can carry
* Genesis Capacity: Maximum Genesis Devices ship can transport
* Special Ability: Unique ship capability or bonus
* Escape Pod: Indestructible survival craft, high turn cost for movement

