  effect: +drone capacity
  max_bonus: +2 bays from base

GenesisContainment:
  effect: +Genesis Device capacity
  max_bonus: +2 devices
  restriction: Only ships with existing Genesis compatibility

INSURANCE_TIERS:
Basic:
  coverage: 50% of ship value
  deductible: 5%
  use_case: Low-risk trading in safe sectors

Standard:
  coverage: 75% of ship value
  deductible: 10%
  use_case: Moderate-risk activities

Premium:
  coverage: 90% of ship value
  deductible: 15%
  use_case: High-risk combat or dangerous sectors

ACQUISITION_METHODS:
Purchase:
  location: Shipyards in major sectors
  advantage: Full customization, new condition

Salvage:
  location: Abandoned or contested sectors
  advantage: Lower cost, potential rare finds
  disadvantage: May require repairs

ReputationRewards:
  location: Faction headquarters
  advantage: Free or discounted, unique configurations
  requirement: High faction standing

ESCAPE_POD:
* Indestructible survival craft, never lost
* Activated automatically on ship destruction
* High turn cost for movement (penalty vs regular ships)
* Zero cargo capacity
* Cannot engage in combat
* Player retains all credits when ejecting
* Can dock at any port to purchase new ship

CONSTRAINTS:
* Ship loss results in cargo destruction, credits retained
* Warp Jumper limited to 1 per player
* Genesis Containment upgrades require existing Genesis compatibility
* Insurance payouts immediate upon destruction
* Speed upgrades cannot exceed engine category maximums
* Drone capacity limited by physical bay space
* Quantum Jump has 24-hour cooldown

